AB  - In this paper, we explore the pricing decision and collection strategy of closed-loop supply chain, in which the manufacturer can offer products through dual channels in the forward logistics, while the recycling competition exists in the reverse logistics. According to the Stackelberg game theory, we characterize the profit functions of closed-loop supply chain with the different scenarios of reverse logistics. By comparing the different scenarios, we provide some suggestions for the waste collection and management.
