TY  - JOUR
AU  - Pal, B
AU  - Guin, S
TI  - A dual-channel closed-loop supply chain coordination with green innovation and sales effort under uncertain market conditions
T2  - INTERNATIONAL JOURNAL OF SYSTEMS SCIENCE-OPERATIONS & LOGISTICS
AB  - Under uncertain circumstances, adopting an option contract within a dual-channel approach emerges as a beneficial strategy for maximising individual profit among the supply chain members. This viewpoint led us to design and examine a dual-channel closed-loop supply chain involving a manufacturer and a retailer. By considering the customer demand is probabilistic and depends on both the product's green innovation level and the retailer-provided sales effort level, we explore three distinct strategies, namely centralised, manufacturer Stackelberg and option contracts, to determine the optimal profits for individual members and the entire supply chain. We present a numerical example illustrating the analytical results to help comprehend the conclusions better. The primary outcome of our study is that when supply chain participants employ option contract techniques and use fixed values for the option price and exercise price, the supply chain as a whole and each supply chain member experience the most favourable outcomes. Additionally, we perform a sensitivity analysis, revealing that the overall supply chain profit positively correlates with the increasing collection rate of end-of-life products. The present study includes insightful information on effectively operating a dual-channel closed-loop supply chain, highlighting the benefits of using option contract strategies.
