AU  - Xu, L
AU  - Shi, J
TI  - The effect of capacity constraint on pricing decision and coordination contract in recycling channels
T2  - RAIRO-OPERATIONS RESEARCH
AB  - Considering the capacity constraints of collection channels, this paper studies a closed-loop supply chain (CLSC) consisting of one manufacturer and two retailers. Based on game theory, we have designed three different scenarios: Neither retailer collections, Only one retailer collections, and Both retailers collection. Among them, in the third scenario, we have more specifically studied the concentration and dispersion of retailers under two-way competition. In these three scenarios, we obtained the equilibrium decisions of the manufacturer and the retailers, and compared the performance in the three scenarios. By analyzing the performance in different scenarios, it is most advantageous for the two retailers to collection at higher production cost savings and lower competition intensity. Therefore, when retailers choose capacity-constrained collection, they often bring significant profit improvement, and when the strategies of the two retailers are inconsistent, the retailer may suffer a loss of profits. Furthermore, we try to coordinate the supply chain through two-part tariff contracts to achieve Pareto improvement.
