TI  - DECISION ANALYSIS OF RECYCLING AND REMANUFACTURING SUPPLY CHAIN: A GAME THEORY APPROACH
T2  - INTERNATIONAL JOURNAL OF TRANSPORT ECONOMICS
AB  - This research analyzed the decision making of different operation modes of remanufacturing supply chain with the consideration of the quality uncertainty. The remanufacturer independently operating remanufacturing supply chain and the recycler and remanufacturer taking cooperation in remanufacturing supply chain operation are both analyzed in this paper. It is found that when the remanufacturer needs to make decision on waste product acquisition and remanufacturing quantity, the remanufacturer's profit can be the highest, but he also needs to undertake the whole remanufacturer's cost burden. The cooperatively decision-making of recycler and remanufacturer can make the remanufacturing supply chain more competitive. Also, the quality of waste products plays a significant role in the optimal number of waste product acquisitions and remanufacturing quantity. It is concluded that the remanufacturer can improve the waste products processing capability when he needs to operate remanufacturing supply chain independently, and the information sharing between recycler and remanufacturer is suggested.
