TY  - JOUR
AU  - Zhang, JL
AU  - Hu, ZP
TI  - Optimization study of county multi-level power grid co-dispatch based on hybrid game considering multivariate source-load interaction
T2  - EXPERT SYSTEMS WITH APPLICATIONS
AB  - The county distribution grid is evolving into a platform for the effective allocation of source, grid, load, and storage resources in the wake of access to distributed energy sources, data centers, and other enormous distributed resources. Digital grid cooperative control and multilayer grid cooperative scheduling are essential methods for achieving energy conservation, reducing consumption in data centers, and enhancing the flexibility of distribution grids. To this end, this paper constructs a county multi-level power grid co-dispatch model based on a hybrid game considering multivariate source-load interaction. Firstly, the active distribution grid system with a data center and the rural microgrid system with biomass waste are constructed. And analyze the coordinated scheduling mechanism of the county main grid, distribution grid and microgrid. Secondly, the analysis of the data center's flexible regulation potential will be carried out, and the demand response model will be constructed. Finally, the county multi-level grid coordinated scheduling optimization model will be built based on a hybrid game under multivariate source-load interaction. The Kriging meta-model is used to solve the master-slave game, and the PR-ADMM algorithm is used to solve the cooperative game. Compared with the traditional solution method, the convergence speed of the hybrid game model is increased by 93.84 %. The results of the example show that after demand response, the load peak-to-valley difference and cost of the distribution network decreased by 22.71 % and 3.02 %, respectively. After the hybrid game, the power transaction cost of MG3 is reduced by 9.91 %, and the carbon trading income is increased by 1.39 %. Therefore, the hybrid game model can improve the coordination, flexibility and low carbon of the county multi-level power grid co- dispatch.
